The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during the swearing-in ceremony of Kelly Craft as the United States Ambassador to Canada. Pence welcomes the guests and highlights the importance of the relationship between the United States and Canada. He praises Craft's qualifications and expresses confidence in her ability to strengthen the alliance. Craft then gives a speech expressing gratitude for the opportunity to serve and emphasizes the importance of leadership and service. She also acknowledges her family and expresses her love and appreciation for her husband.